Hacker School Soylent 1.0
30 day amount to use for 1 person, split into special containers for single serving size.

Ingredients
3600 g oat flour (8 pounds)
2550 g soy protein, Trader Joe's, unflavored (3 Tubs)
2550 g olive oil
2250 g brown sugar (5 pounds)
750 g ground flax (1.6 pounds | 26.5 oz)
600 g cocoa powder (1.3 pound | 21 oz )
450 g lecithin (.99 pound | 16 oz)
60 g iodized salt
30 g Emergen-C(3 or 4 packs)


1 vitamin D supplement
Up to 10 g potassium citrate or suppliments.

Method

Combine all dry ingredients except Vitamin D and potassium citrate. Mix well.
Single meal is approximately 120g of dry mix.
Oil amount per serving is approximately 28g.
Add 400-500 ml (14-16 oz) of water, and shake or stir well.
Chill for several hours if possible, to improve taste and texture. It may be healthier that way too (due to phytic acid deactivation).
Meanwhile, take your Vitamin D and/or get some sunshine.
Drink.
